                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5920: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-24T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 24, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 24—12:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178. Following from American Consul General Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 23, 5 p.m. Japanese military state that volunteer commander Liu
                            Kuei-tang and approximately 18,000 of his men surrendered at Lupei near
                            Tungliao and joined the Manchukuo army. Commercial aeroplanes of the
                            Manchukuo air service will be used for transporting army supplies to the
                            front.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
